<doc id="55812" wikidata="Q7003044" url="?curid=55812" title="Neutrality Act">
<text>Neutrality Act may refer to:
* Proclamation of Neutrality, 1793, declared the US neutral in the conflict between France and Great Britain
* Neutrality Act of 1794, makes it illegal for an American to wage war against any country at peace with the US
* Neutrality Act of 1818
* Neutrality Acts of the 1930s, passed by Congress in the 1930s in response to turmoil in Europe and Asia</text><links>
<link wikidata="Q1981888" start="31" end="57" title="Proclamation of Neutrality" label="Proclamation of Neutrality"/>
<link wikidata="Q7003047" start="140" end="162" title="Neutrality Act of 1794" label="Neutrality Act of 1794"/>
<link wikidata="Q112051822" start="252" end="274" title="Neutrality Act of 1818" label="Neutrality Act of 1818"/>
<link wikidata="Q914092" start="277" end="305" title="Neutrality Acts of the 1930s" label="Neutrality Acts of the 1930s"/>
